{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1770133131,"nonce":"jePzfhZYQXmBB3Buh2uoqgcRagQ=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87n-Vz2","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/145","origin":"github"},"title":"Agents bypass gh_create_issue.sh wrapper and use gh directly","message":"## Problem\n\nAgents are calling `gh issue create` directly instead of using the provided wrapper script `.agent/scripts/gh_create_issue.sh`, which defeats its purpose of label validation.\n\n**Example**: In Issue #144, I attempted to use `--label 'process'` which failed because that label doesn't exist. The wrapper script would have caught this before submission.\n\n## Current State\n\n**Infrastructure exists but is ignored**:\n- ✅ `.agent/scripts/gh_create_issue.sh` - Validates labels against metadata\n- ✅ `.agent/github_metadata.json` - Lists valid labels  \n- ✅ `CLI_COMMANDS.md` - Documents the wrapper script\n- ❌ **Agents ignore the wrapper and call `gh issue create` directly**\n\n## Root Cause\n\nAgent instructions don't explicitly require using the wrapper script. The instructions mention it exists, but don't mandate its use.\n\nFrom `.github/copilot-instructions.md`:\n- Shows `gh` CLI examples\n- Doesn't prohibit direct `gh issue create` calls\n- Doesn't mandate wrapper usage\n\n## Impact\n\nWhen agents bypass the wrapper:\n1. Invalid labels cause `gh issue create` to fail\n2. Agent must retry without the label\n3. Wastes time and creates noisy command history\n4. Defeats the purpose of Issue #111's solution\n\n## Proposed Solution\n\n### Option 1: Hard Requirement in Instructions\nAdd explicit rule to `.agent/AI_RULES.md`:\n\n```markdown\n**GitHub Issue Creation**:\n- MUST use `.agent/scripts/gh_create_issue.sh` wrapper (not `gh issue create` directly)\n- Wrapper validates labels against `.agent/github_metadata.json`\n- Direct `gh issue create` calls are PROHIBITED for agents\n```\n\n### Option 2: Add to Copilot Instructions\nUpdate `.github/copilot-instructions.md` with:\n\n```markdown\nWhen creating GitHub issues:\n1. Read `.agent/github_metadata.json` to see valid labels\n2. Use `.agent/scripts/gh_create_issue.sh` wrapper (REQUIRED)\n3. Never call `gh issue create` directly\n```\n\n### Option 3: Both (Recommended)\n- Update AI_RULES.md for all agents\n- Update copilot-instructions.md for Copilot CLI specifically\n- Add examples showing wrapper usage\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- ✅ Agent instructions explicitly require wrapper usage\n- ✅ Direct `gh issue create` usage is documented as prohibited\n- ✅ Examples in documentation use wrapper script\n- ✅ Clear enforcement language (MUST/REQUIRED, not SHOULD)\n\n## Related Issues\n\n- #111 - Created the wrapper script and metadata file (closed, completed)\n- #144 - Model identity issue (similar pattern: resources exist but aren't used)\n\n## Pattern\n\nThis is part of a broader pattern where agents have tools/resources available but don't use them:\n- Model identity: `set_git_identity_env.sh` returns 'Unknown' → should ask user\n- Label validation: `gh_create_issue.sh` exists → should use it, not bypass\n\nBoth need explicit enforcement in instructions.\n\n---\n**AI Signature**  \nAgent: Copilot CLI Agent  \nModel: claude-sonnet-4.5  \nContext: Self-reported friction, demonstrating correct wrapper usage","files":null}]}